---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SpeakerModal from '../../components/SpeakerModal.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Oxford LLMs 2023"
  description="Oxford LLMs 2023 — the inaugural workshop on large language models for social science. Nuffield College, September 2023."
>

  <!-- ── Breadcrumb strip ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <aside class="status-strip" aria-label="Page breadcrumb">
    <div class="status-strip-inner">
      <a href="/summer-school/" style="color:inherit; text-decoration:none;">Summer School</a>
      <span class="sep"></span>
      <span>2023 — Inaugural edition</span>
    </div>
  </aside>

  <!-- ── Report hero ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="report-hero">
    <div class="rh-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="rh-kicker">Inaugural edition · September 2023</p>
        <span class="rh-year">2023</span>
        <p class="rh-title">The first Oxford school on large language models for social science.</p>
        <div class="rh-stats">
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">~30</span><span class="rh-l">Participants</span></div>
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">5</span><span class="rh-l">Days</span></div>
          <div class="rh-stat"><span class="rh-n">3</span><span class="rh-l">Conveners</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rh-photo">
        <img src="/img/posts/report_2023/group_llms_2023.jpg" alt="Oxford LLMs 2023 inaugural cohort at Nuffield College" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── § 01 About ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="about">
    <span class="section-number">§ 01 · About</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Inaugural edition</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">Where it started.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          The first Oxford school on Large Language Models for Social Science brought together
          around 30 PhD students and postdocs from across the world for a week at Nuffield College.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width: 72ch;">
        <p class="copy" style="margin: 0 0 18px;">
          The school attracted significant interest and welcomed an exceptionally diverse cohort
          of early-career researchers eager to explore advanced text analysis and AI methods.
          <a href="https://lena-voita.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elena Voita</a> delivered
          the core lecture series, tracing the history of NLP from early rule-based systems to modern
          Transformer architectures and alignment methods.
        </p>
        <p class="copy" style="margin: 0 0 32px;">
          Ilya Boytsov led the hands-on workshops, coding online to a live in-person audience after
          visa issues prevented him from attending in person, in what participants still remember as
          an unexpectedly memorable format. All materials were published openly on GitHub so that a
          wider audience could benefit from the school, a commitment that has stayed constant in
          every edition since.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- 2-photo spread: lecture and seminar -->
      <div class="photo-spread reveal">
        <img src="/img/posts/report_2023/lecture_2023.jpg" alt="Lecture session at Oxford LLMs 2023" />
        <img src="/img/posts/report_2023/seminar_2023.jpg" alt="Seminar session at Oxford LLMs 2023" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 02 People ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker section-tinted-v3" id="people">
    <span class="section-number">§ 02 · People</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Conveners &amp; organiser</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">The team behind the inaugural school.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">Click any card to read the full profile.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="speaker-grid reveal-stagger">

        <button class="speaker-chip" data-speaker="elena-voita" data-name="Elena Voita" data-role="Research Scientist, FAIR (Meta AI)" data-tag="Convener · Lecturer" data-initials="EV">
          <div class="sc-portrait">EV</div>
          <div class="sc-info"><span class="sc-tag">Convener · Lecturer</span><p class="sc-name">Elena Voita</p><p class="sc-role">Research Scientist, FAIR (Meta AI)</p></div>
        </button>

        <button class="speaker-chip" data-speaker="ilya-boytsov" data-name="Ilya Boytsov" data-role="NLP Lead, Wayfair" data-tag="Convener · Workshop" data-initials="IB">
          <div class="sc-portrait">IB</div>
          <div class="sc-info"><span class="sc-tag">Convener · Workshop</span><p class="sc-name">Ilya Boytsov</p><p class="sc-role">NLP Lead, Wayfair</p></div>
        </button>

        <button class="speaker-chip" data-speaker="maksim-zubok" data-name="Maksim Zubok" data-role="DPIR, Oxford" data-tag="Organiser" data-img="/img/speakers/maksim_zubok.png">
          <div class="sc-portrait"><img src="/img/speakers/maksim_zubok.png" alt="" /></div>
          <div class="sc-info"><span class="sc-tag">Organiser</span><p class="sc-name">Maksim Zubok</p><p class="sc-role">DPIR, Oxford</p></div>
        </button>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── § 03 Materials ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section-v3 section-v3--marker" id="materials" style="padding-bottom: clamp(56px, 7vw, 88px);">
    <span class="section-number">§ 03 · Materials</span>
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head-v3 reveal">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow-v3" style="margin-bottom:14px">Open access</div>
          <h2 class="h-section">Slides and notebooks.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede-v3">
          All lecture notes, coding exercises, and presentation slides from the inaugural school
          are freely available on GitHub.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <a class="fb" href="https://github.com/antndlcrx/oxford-llms-workshop" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="display:block; max-width: 480px;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:10px;">
            <img src="/img/icons/github-mark.svg" alt="" style="width:24px; height:24px; opacity:0.85;">
            <h3 class="h-sub" style="margin:0;">Workshop materials</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="copy" style="margin:0 0 12px; font-size:14px;">Lecture slides, Python notebooks, and exercise code from the 2023 inaugural edition.</p>
          <span class="btn-link-v3">Open on GitHub <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:40px; display:flex; gap:24px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a class="btn-ghost" href="/summer-school/2024/">2024 edition →</a>
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/summer-school/">All cohorts <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Bio data (used by speaker modal) ───────────────────── -->
  <div hidden aria-hidden="true">

    <div id="bio-elena-voita">
      <p><a href="https://lena-voita.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elena Voita</a> is a Research Scientist at FAIR (Meta AI). She is widely known in the NLP community for her accessible writing and her illustrated NLP course at <a href="https://lena-voita.github.io/nlp_course.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">lena-voita.github.io</a>, which has reached a global audience of self-learners and students.</p>
      <p>At the inaugural school, she delivered the core lecture series, tracing the history of NLP from rule-based systems to modern Transformer architectures and alignment techniques. Her talks connected theory to current research practice and set the intellectual foundation for the week.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="bio-ilya-boytsov">
      <p>Ilya Boytsov is an applied Deep Learning Scientist and NLP Lead at Wayfair in Berlin. His main professional interests include information retrieval, aspect-based sentiment analysis, and generative AI. He has extensive experience designing machine-learning bootcamps and lectures for diverse audiences.</p>
      <p>At the 2023 school, visa issues prevented him from attending in person. He led the hands-on workshops online to a live in-person audience, a format that turned an obstacle into something participants found unexpectedly effective. He is also co-founder of the Street Smart AI community in Berlin.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="bio-maksim-zubok">
      <p>Maksim Zubok is a doctoral candidate in Politics at Oxford University, <a href="https://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/people/profiles/maksim-zubok/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nuffield College</a>. His research explores how large language models can be used for social science, from standard data labelling tasks to using models as snapshots of the internet to study how people structure concepts and beliefs.</p>
      <p>He conceived and organised the inaugural school in 2023, and has led the programme through each edition since. He has also helped organise the <a href="https://sicss.io/2022/oxford/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oxford Summer Institute for Computational Social Science</a>.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <SpeakerModal />

</Base>
